name: KUROSHIRO No. 1
description:
Sighting number 1

"Dino's Attack!"

Fri. Jan 28, 2022, 14:11
This photo was taken on a winter sunny day in Landungsbrücken, Hamburg. I was on my way to get my third vaccine dose when I saw this green monstrous figure grab a person with its hand. This figure turns out to be called REKKUSU and it lives underground within the sewers. REKKUSU is a mixture of a dinosaur and a lizard and it can swim swiftly with the help of its fins. It eats mostly fish but it gets angry because the sewers are being contaminated.
 
---------------------------
KURO means black in Japanese and SHIRO means white.

KUROSHIRO is a series of black and white pictures with a doodle of sightings all around Germany. These pictures were all taken by a Google Pixel 5.

2268 x 2268
